data.text:
Wedding of Princess Bathildis of Schaumburg-Lippe and Prince Friedrich of Waldeck and Pyrmont in Náchod, Bohemia. (9.8.1895).

Back row: Prince Maximilian of Schaumburg-Lippe, Prince Frederick of Schaumburg-Lippe and Prince Albrecht of Schaumburg-Lippe.

Front row: Queen Charlotte of Württemberg née Schaumburg-Lippe, Princess Pauline of Württemberg, Princess Elisabeth of Waldeck and Pyrmont, Bride's mother Princess Bathildis of Schaumburg-Lippe née Anhalt, Princess Adelaide of Schaumburg-Lippe, Bride: Princess Bathildis of Schaumburg-Lippe, Bridegroom: Prince Friedrich of Waldeck and Pyrmont, Princess Alexandra of Schaumburg-Lippe, Princess Pauline of Bentheim and Steinfurt née Waldeck and Pyrmont, Princess Helena Duchess of Albany, Bridegroom's stepmother Princess Louise of Waldeck and Pyrmont née Schleswig-Holstein-Sonderburg-Glücksburg, King William II of Württemberg and Bride's father Prince William of Schaumburg-Lippe.

Prince Friedrich was a brother of Helena, Duchess of Albany and a maternal cousin of King Gustav V of Sweden.

I have yet to identify the lady behind Princess Bathildis and the man behind Princess Pauline of Bentheim and Steinfurt.

Source: Czech Archives
